# ApexTree — AI Coding Rules

You are working with ApexTree, a JavaScript organizational / hierarchical tree-chart library built on SVG.
Documentation: https://apexcharts.com/docs/apextree/
NPM: apextree
GitHub: https://github.com/apexcharts/apextree

## Critical Rules

1. **Data goes to `render(rootNode)`, not the constructor.** Constructor takes `(element, options)`.
2. **Every node has `id`, `name`, `children`.** Leaves have `children: []` (empty array, not omitted).
3. **`id` must be unique across the entire tree.**
4. **`render()` returns a `Graph`.** Keep it — it exposes `collapse`, `expand`, search, selection, layout APIs.
5. **`enableSelection` is `'single' | 'multi' | false`**, not a boolean.
6. **Selection callbacks are on the `Graph`**: `graph.onSelectionChange(fn)`, not in options.
7. **Use `contentKey: 'data'` for the built-in org-card template** — don't hand-roll the avatar / title / subtitle layout.
8. **`direction` is `'top' | 'bottom' | 'left' | 'right'`.**
9. **Call `destroy()`** before unmounting in React / Vue / Angular.
10. **Set license once** with `ApexTree.setLicense('KEY')` at app startup.

---

## Data Format

```ts
interface NestedNode<T = undefined> {
  id: string;                       // REQUIRED, globally unique
  name: string;                     // REQUIRED, label when contentKey === 'name'
  children: NestedNode<T>[];        // REQUIRED, [] for leaves
  data?: T;                         // payload used when contentKey === 'data'
  options?: Partial<NodeOptions & FontOptions & TooltipOptions>;
}
```

```js
import { ApexTree } from 'apextree';

const data = {
  id: '1', name: 'CEO',
  children: [
    { id: '2', name: 'CTO', children: [
      { id: '4', name: 'Eng Lead', children: [] },
    ]},
    { id: '3', name: 'CFO', children: [] },
  ],
};

const tree = new ApexTree(document.getElementById('chart'), {
  width: 800, height: 600,
  nodeWidth: 120, nodeHeight: 40,
  childrenSpacing: 70, siblingSpacing: 30,
  direction: 'top',
});
const graph = tree.render(data);
```

### Org-card mode

```js
new ApexTree(el, {
  contentKey: 'data',
  nodeWidth: 220, nodeHeight: 80,
}).render({
  id: 'ceo', name: 'Alice',
  data: {
    name: 'Alice Johnson',
    title: 'CEO',
    subtitle: 'Executive',
    imageURL: 'https://...',
    accentColor: '#6366f1',
    badge: { text: 'Active', color: '#EEF2FF' },
  },
  children: [],
});
```

---

## Lifecycle

```js
import { ApexTree } from 'apextree';
ApexTree.setLicense('KEY');                    // once at app startup
const tree  = new ApexTree(el, options);
const graph = tree.render(rootNode);           // REQUIRED, keep the Graph
graph.changeLayout('left');
graph.collapse('node-2');
graph.construct(newData);                      // replace data, re-render
tree.destroy();                                // before unmount
```

---

## API

### Tree

| Method | Description |
|---|---|
| `new ApexTree(el, opts?)` | Construct. |
| `render(root)` | Paint. Returns `Graph`. Required. |
| `destroy()` | Tear down. |
| `ApexTree.setLicense(key)` | Static; call once. |

### Graph

| Method | Description |
|---|---|
| `construct(data)` | Replace data + re-render. |
| `changeLayout(direction)` | Switch direction. |
| `collapse(id)` / `expand(id)` | Programmatic expand/collapse. |
| `fitScreen()` | Re-fit viewBox. |
| `centerOnNode(id)` | Pan/zoom to node. |
| `getNodeMap()` / `getRootNodeId()` / `getNodeLabel(id)` | Introspection. |
| `findNodesByQuery(q)` / `setSearchHighlight(ids)` | Search. |
| `getSelection()` / `setSelection(ids)` / `clearSelection()` | Selection. |
| `onSelectionChange(fn)` | Subscribe. `null` to unsubscribe. |
| `setBreadcrumbHandler(fn)` | Breadcrumb segment click. |
| `exportToSvg()` | SVG download. |

---

## Pitfalls — ❌ Wrong vs ✅ Correct

### 1. Data on constructor
❌ `new ApexTree(el, rootNode)`
✅ `new ApexTree(el, options).render(rootNode)`

### 2. Missing `children: []`
❌ `{ id: 'leaf', name: 'X' }` — iteration errors.
✅ `{ id: 'leaf', name: 'X', children: [] }`

### 3. Duplicate ids
❌ Two `{ id: 'a' }` nodes anywhere in the tree.
✅ Globally unique ids.

### 4. Missing `render()`
❌ Just constructing.
✅ `tree.render(data)`.

### 5. `enableSelection: true`
❌ Type error / no selection.
✅ `enableSelection: 'single'` or `'multi'`.

### 6. Selection callback in options
❌ `new ApexTree(el, { onSelectionChange })`.
✅ `graph.onSelectionChange((ids) => ...)`.

### 7. Hand-rolling the org-card layout
❌ Custom `nodeTemplate` for avatar / title / subtitle.
✅ `contentKey: 'data'` + structured `data: { name, title, subtitle, imageURL, accentColor, badge }`.

### 8. No `destroy()` on unmount
❌ Observer leak.
✅ Return `() => tree.destroy()` from cleanup.

### 9. Full reconstruct just to swap data
❌ `tree.destroy(); new ApexTree(el, opts).render(newData)`.
✅ `graph.construct(newData)`.

### 10. Mutating the tree in place
❌ `data.children.push(newChild)` — no update.
✅ `graph.construct({ ...data, children: [...data.children, newChild] })`.

### 11. Hover shows nothing
❌ `enableTooltip` defaults to `false`.
✅ Set `enableTooltip: true` and (optionally) supply `tooltipTemplate`.

### 12. License watermark
❌ Skipping `setLicense`.
✅ `ApexTree.setLicense('KEY')` once at app startup.

---

## Framework Wrappers

```bash
npm install react-apextree   # React
npm install vue-apextree     # Vue 3
npm install ngx-apextree     # Angular
```

All wrappers handle `destroy()` automatically on unmount.
